# What is LangChain 

## Example 
- [ ] Reference this website [pdf.ai](https://pdf.ai/)

If we were to recreate the app we have 2 high level options: 

### Option 1: Take all text and send it to ChatGPT

### Option 2: Take send relevant chunks to ChatGPT
- [ ] Takes pdf content and parses into Chunks
- [ ] Chunks get sent to an Embedding Creation Algorithm 
- [ ] All embeddings are an Array of numbers between -1 and 1 representing the chunk
- [ ] The Arrays are effectively text summaries the describe in multi-dimenstions what the chunk represents
- [ ] Once the embeddings are created they are stored in a Vector Store
- [ ] Now when a question is asked, the question is also turned into an embedding -- now we can look for a chunk of text that is most similar to our chunk
- [ ] Now both the 1. question embedding & 2. the most similar chunk embedding coming from the vector store are both sent to the LLM via a prompt template
- [ ] Now the LLM applies some inference on the question along with the most relevant chunk, which generally makes the LLM the list interesting portion 

The LLM is effectively validating/or parroting back what it found from the chunk.

----

So in this example what is the point of LangChain? 

- [ ] LangChain gives us a mechanism to automate each one of these steps into a flow that allows for each piece of this process to be executed in the order intended. 

1. Use uploads pdf
```python
from langchain.document_loaders import UnstructuredPDFLoader

loader = UnstructuedPDFLoader("earth.pdf")
data = loader.load()
print(data)
```

